# lead-b2iz (P1 bug) — pins the corrected behavior for the fresh-adopter
# bootstrap regression. ROOT CAUSE: the rendered "bin/bootstrap" floats the
# bc-lead/bc-base image on a tag and "docker pull"s it, then PROCEEDS to render
# regardless of whether the pull fetched a current image — so a stale/cached
# ":latest" (or a silent pull/auth fallback to cache) makes the in-image
# "shop-templates bootstrap" render an ANCIENT shop (no AGENT_VAULT_CA_PEM,
# hardcoded product name, pre-<changeme> style). These scenarios pin the gate
# that closes that gap: bootstrap READS the pulled image's baked shop-templates
# version and only renders when it meets an expected minimum; otherwise it
# refuses loudly instead of silently rendering an ancient shop.
#
# ENABLER (already shipped): PDR-026 / lead-5xnd bakes the version into the
# published images as inspectable provenance — OCI label
# "shopsystem.shop-templates.version" and container ENV "SHOP_TEMPLATES_VERSION"
# (verified live on v0.3.40 / templates 0.48.0). That makes the read CHEAP
# (docker image inspect / printenv) WITHOUT invoking python/pip in the image —
# exactly the consumer PDR-026 named for this bead.
#
# DELIVERY LINKAGE (architect): "bin/bootstrap" is RENDERED from shop-templates
# (the templates/ops bootstrap entry), so the fix is a shop-templates template
# change; but adopters receive "bin/bootstrap" via the starter fork
# (dstengle/shopsystem-starter), which is STALE per lead-x4mk — so reaching
# adopters ALSO needs the starter re-render (lead-x4mk). Cross-ref lead-ko2v
# (bc-container launch uses cached :latest — same stale-:latest class) and
# lead-5xnd (the provenance enabler).
#
# SCOPE THINNESS (flag for architect): "expected-minimum shop-templates version
# known to bin/bootstrap" pins the MECHANISM (read baked version, compare to a
# declared floor, gate). WHERE that floor is set/updated (a hardcoded constant
# re-rendered each release vs. sourced from a pinned coordinate vs. the starter's
# own pinned version) is a policy left to decomposition — pinned here only as
# "known to bin/bootstrap".
#
# @bc: and the reproducing @scenario_hash on dispatch are the Architect's; the
# block-only @scenario_hash below is the PO's authoring hash.

Feature: bin/bootstrap verifies the pulled image's baked shop-templates version before rendering

@scenario_hash:4457c8c280d4fbf4
Scenario: bootstrap reads the pulled image's baked shop-templates version and proceeds when it meets the expected minimum
  Given an adopter fork whose "bin/bootstrap" resolves the bc-lead/bc-base image on a floating tag
  And the pulled image carries baked shop-templates provenance per PDR-026 — the OCI label "shopsystem.shop-templates.version" and the container ENV "SHOP_TEMPLATES_VERSION"
  And that baked shop-templates version is at or above the expected-minimum shop-templates version known to "bin/bootstrap"
  When the adopter runs "bin/bootstrap" and it pulls the image
  Then bootstrap reads the baked shop-templates version from the pulled image's provenance via a "docker image inspect" read of the "shopsystem.shop-templates.version" label (or a "printenv SHOP_TEMPLATES_VERSION" read of a container started from it), without invoking "pip show" or any python in the image
  And because the read version is at or above the expected minimum, bootstrap proceeds to render the shop via the in-image "shop-templates bootstrap"

@scenario_hash:e9d64a8acc917efb
Scenario: bootstrap refuses to render and exits loudly when the pulled image's baked shop-templates version is below the expected minimum
  Given an adopter fork whose "bin/bootstrap" resolves the bc-lead/bc-base image on a floating tag
  And the pull resolves a stale or cached image whose baked shop-templates version — read from the PDR-026 "shopsystem.shop-templates.version" label or "SHOP_TEMPLATES_VERSION" ENV — is below the expected-minimum shop-templates version known to "bin/bootstrap"
  When the adopter runs "bin/bootstrap" and it pulls that stale image
  Then bootstrap does not invoke the in-image "shop-templates bootstrap" render step against the stale image, so no shop is rendered from it
  And bootstrap exits non-zero with a diagnostic that names the stale baked shop-templates version it read, the expected-minimum version it required, and an actionable remediation for obtaining the current image
